parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the automatic shoulder belt can increase the risk of injury or death in the event of a crash, as the belt may not properly restrain the occupant.
symptoms: The shoulder belt fails to retract
the shoulder belt is stuck in the midway position
the shoulder belt does not move in the forward position
the motorized seat belt retractor is inoperative
the seat belt will not retract towards the body when the door is closed
the lap/shoulder belt fails due to a faulty cable
the cable comes out of the retractor
the buckle failure
the latching mechanism is broken
the motor burns out
the passive restraint shoulder belts fail
and the retractor jams in the up position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inability to obtain recall repairs can leave the vehicle in an unsafe condition, increasing the risk of injury or death in the event of a crash.
symptoms: The dealership claims that no parts are available for the recall repair
the manufacturer does not know when more parts will be available
the dealer pulls the seat belt apart and does not complete the work due to no parts.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Pulsation Damper Failure Leading to Engine Fire
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the pulsation damper can cause engine fires, which can lead to serious accidents, injuries, or even fatalities. It can also result in significant engine damage, requiring costly repairs or even replacement.
symptoms: Unusual smells or odors from the engine
engine overheating
engine fire
loss of engine power
engine failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the windshield wiper switch can cause the wipers to malfunction, leading to poor visibility, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The windshield wiper switch only operates at one speed
typically the top speed
the wipers do not stop in the down position
the wipers malfunction
causing visual difficulty.
